<cell id="cell-0"><language>kotlin</language>// Kotlin notebook
import jline.*
import jline.lang.*
import jline.lang.nodes.*
import jline.lang.processes.*
import jline.lang.constant.*
import jline.solvers.mva.*
import jline.util.matrix.*</cell id="cell-0">
<cell id="cell-1"><language>kotlin</language>// Define the workflow
val wf = Workflow("APHWorkflow")</cell id="cell-1">
<cell id="cell-2"><language>kotlin</language>// Add activities with different SCVs using APH
val A = wf.addActivity("A", APH.fitMeanAndSCV(1.0, 0.5))   // Low variability
val B = wf.addActivity("B", APH.fitMeanAndSCV(2.0, 2.0))   // High variability
val C = wf.addActivity("C", APH.fitMeanAndSCV(1.5, 1.0))   // Standard variability</cell id="cell-2">
<cell id="cell-3"><language>kotlin</language>// Define serial precedence
wf.addPrecedence(Workflow.serial(A, B, C))</cell id="cell-3">
<cell id="cell-4"><language>kotlin</language>// Convert to phase-type distribution
val ph = wf.toPH()</cell id="cell-4">
<cell id="cell-5"><language>kotlin</language>// Display results
println("APH Workflow: A -> B -> C")
println("Activity A: APH(mean=1.0, SCV=0.5)")
println("Activity B: APH(mean=2.0, SCV=2.0)")
println("Activity C: APH(mean=1.5, SCV=1.0)")
println("Expected total mean: ${1.0 + 2.0 + 1.5}")
println("Computed PH mean: ${ph.mean}")
println("Computed PH SCV: ${ph.sCV}")
println("Number of phases: ${ph.subgenerator.getNumRows()}")</cell id="cell-5">
<cell id="cell-6"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type>## Workflow with APH Distributions

A workflow using APH (Acyclic Phase-Type) distributions for flexible variability modeling.

**Workflow:** A -> B -> C

This example demonstrates:
- Using APH distributions to fit both mean and SCV (squared coefficient of variation)
- APH provides flexibility to model any combination of mean and SCV
- Activity A has low variability (SCV=0.5, sub-exponential)
- Activity B has high variability (SCV=2.0, hyper-exponential)
- Activity C has standard variability (SCV=1.0, exponential)
- The resulting phase-type distribution captures the combined variability of all activities</cell id="cell-6"></cell>